carne asada.review:
fue un dia de suerte!!!!

tuve suerte de parquearme al frente: omg! a parking space in the mission??!!! and in front of the taqueria?!!;

tuve suerte que quedo una mesa: this place can get really packed in a blink of an eye and a table near the cd player was  meant for us to have it!!;

fue grandioso probar burrito: delicious, zestful fillings of grilled chicken and carne asada satisfied our cravings. the meats are tender, juicy and it wasn't greasy nor salty at all!;

y de tener grandiosos empleados: welcoming and courteous staff!  i also like the way they cater to you, by bringing the nachos and the spicy chipotle (?) dip to your table together with the fork/knife.

definitely a place i will frequent!

